startElement

public void startElement(java.lang.String namespaceURI,
                         java.lang.String localName,
                         java.lang.String qName,
                         org.xml.sax.Attributes atts)
startElement: Called when a comp element is found. This uses the xsi:type attribute to determine which Presenter to switch contexts with: IVL, PIVL, SXPR. As of now, the xsi:type is mandatory. In the future, this will not be mandatory and SXPR will implement Datatypable. Then, if xsi:type is not specified, the Datatype can be used to delegate.
